article.headline: Jacksonville 71, Campbell 58
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Keith McDougald scored 15 points to lead five Jacksonville players in double figures in a 71-58 win over Campbell on Monday night. Ayron Hardy added 11 points and Delwan Graham, Travis Cohn and Russell Powell chipped in 10 each for the Dolphins (14-6, 8-3 Atlantic Sun Conference). Jacksonville, which scored 20 points off 18 turnovers, had six blocked shots, with Glenn Powell getting four. The Camels had as many blocks as Powell, coming a little less than one shy of their conference-leading average (5.14 a game coming in). Campbell is now six shy of the school record of 117 set in 1997-98. The Dolphins shot 50 percent from the field in the first half (11 of 22), while holding the Campbell to just 9 of 26 to take a 32-27 lead at halftime. Campbell (11-11, 5-7) had just six assists, compared to 14 by Jacksonville. Eric Griffin led the Camels with 21 points.
